OL,3,CFerry worker endangered lives in fatal
OL,4,Cboat collision, jury finds
OL,6,FMr Shearwood explained: "Sadly, when
OL,7,Fwe were able to recover L'Ecume II and
OL,8,FMichael, the damage that had been
OL,9,Fcaused due to the weather and due to
OL,10,Fthe movement with the tides meant (the
OL,11,Ffishing lights) were not available to
OL,12,Fuse as a piece of evidence, and we
OL,13,Fwere unable to recover them.
OL,15,F"The same goes for the fuse board -
OL,16,Fthey were two key pieces of evidence
OL,17,Fwhich may have been able to tell us if
OL,18,Fthe green light had been illuminated
OL,19,Fat the time, and that would have
OL,20,Fremoved one of the key issues in the
OL,21,Fcase."
