OL,4,Cboat collision, jury finds
OL,6,FDuring the trial, the court heard how
OL,7,FCarr had sent Mr Sevash-Zade away for
OL,8,Fbreakfast before the collision, who
OL,9,Fthen went onto the Goodwill's bridge
OL,10,Fwings to perform other tasks.
OL,12,FMr Sevash-Zade told the court on
OL,13,FFriday 19 September, that he had "no
OL,14,Fconcerns" that "the situation was
OL,15,Fgrowing into a dangerous one", minutes
OL,16,Fbefore a deadly collision.
